casebody.data:
ROGERS v. GUIEREN. On Certiorari. MATTER OF PRACTICE. J. W. Miller for the defendant in Certiorari,

confessed the errors assigned, and consented to a reversal of the judgment.

Mr. Seofidd, attorney of the plaintiff in Certiorari,

declined moving for the reversal.

By the Court.

Let the Clerk enter the reversal of the judgment, as on motion for the plaintiff.
